{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Add Meerkats to the Dangerous Wild Animals Act 1976",
        "additional_details": "Meerkats are social animals. In our view, in the UK, they are sold with less regulation than dogs, leading to a \"fad pet\" crisis. For meerkats, isolation from other meerkats can cause self-harm and psychological shutdown. This mirrors primates, which the Govt recently protected due to their social complexity.",
        "background": "Add Meerkats (Suricata suricatta) to the Schedule of the Dangerous Wild Animals Act 1976. This will end their unregulated sale in pet shops and require any owner to hold a specialist license and we think, mean only those who can provide for their complex \"mob\" social needs to purchase them.",
